I think those who complained about the missing seeder didn't download this torrent (and of course didn't realize).
There was another torrent with the same name for some minutes, then it's been deleted and this one appeared.
I'm not writing this to justify those who complained, but maybe this can explain why they were not downloading.

ursule: you might be right, but I think it was the usual misunderstandings: even if everything is working, it might take a while to connect to a tracker, especially if its under heavy load (as often is the case with TPB), or if its temporarily down.

and it takes even longer connecting torrents through DHT (trackerless). 

and on top of that then we also have all those possibilities with wrong settings at the users side and ISP problems, etc...
